#, no-wrap
msgid "Project Manager"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/projectmgr.md:17
#, no-wrap
msgid "One of the features that an IDE must surely have is the ability to manage the various projects that a developer or publisher works on. Being able to select the project to work on once NvChad is open, without the need to type commands in the *statusline* to achieve the goal. This saves time and allows for simplified management in the case of a large number of projects.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/projectmgr.md:19
#, no-wrap
msgid "Using [charludo/projectmgr.nvim](https://github.com/charludo/projectmgr.nvim) will integrate this functionality. The plugin provides excellent integration with `Telescope` and some interesting additional features such as the ability to synchronize a *git* repository when opening the *project*.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/projectmgr.md:21
#, no-wrap
msgid "The plugin also tracks the status of the editor when it closes allowing you to have, when you next open it, all the pages you were working on.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/projectmgr.md:22
#, no-wrap
msgid "Plugin installation"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/projectmgr.md:25
#, no-wrap
msgid "To install the plugin you will need to edit the **custom/plugins.lua** file by adding the following block of code:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (lua)
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/projectmgr.md:26
#, no-wrap
msgid "{\n"
"    \"charludo/projectmgr.nvim\",\n"
"    lazy = false, -- important!\n"
"},\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/projectmgr.md:34
#, no-wrap
msgid "Once you have saved the file, the plugin will be available for installation. To install it open *lazy.nvim* with the command `:Lazy` and type <kbd>I</kbd>. Once the installation finishes you will have to exit the editor and reopen it to have it read the new configuration you entered.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/projectmgr.md:36
#, no-wrap
msgid "The plugin provides a single command `:ProjectMgr` that opens an interactive buffer from which you can perform all operations by using keyboard shortcuts. When first opened, the buffer will be empty as this screenshot shows:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/projectmgr.md:38
#, no-wrap
msgid "![ProjectMgr Init](./images/projectmgr_init.png)\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/projectmgr.md:39
#, no-wrap
msgid "Using the Project Manager"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/projectmgr.md:42
#, no-wrap
msgid "All operations are performed with the <kbd>Ctrl</kbd> key followed by a letter (e.g. `<C-a`), while the `<CR>` key corresponds to the <kbd>Enter</kbd> key.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/projectmgr.md:44
#, no-wrap
msgid "The following table shows all available operations\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/projectmgr.md:52
#, no-wrap
msgid "| Key     | Operation                                       |\n"
"|-------- | ----------------------------------------------- |\n"
"| `<CR>`  | Opens the project under the cursor              |\n"
"| `<C-a>` | Adds a project through an interactive procedure |\n"
"| `<C-d>` | Delete a project                                |\n"
"| `<C-e>` | Change project settings                         |\n"
"| `<C-q>` | Close buffer                                    |\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/projectmgr.md:54
#, no-wrap
msgid "To add your first project you will need to use the combination <kbd>Ctrl</kbd> + <kbd>a</kbd> which will open an interactive menu in the *statusline*. In this example a clone of the Rocky Linux documentation saved in **~/lab/rockydocs/documentation** will be used.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/projectmgr.md:56
#, no-wrap
msgid "The first question will ask you for the name of the project:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/projectmgr.md:58
#, no-wrap
msgid "> Project Name: documentation\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/projectmgr.md:60
#, no-wrap
msgid "It will follow the project path:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/projectmgr.md:62
#, no-wrap
msgid "> Project Path: ~/lab/rockydocs/documentation/\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/projectmgr.md:64
#, no-wrap
msgid "This is followed by the ability to set commands to be run when opening and closing the project. These commands refer to those executable in the editor and not to the **bash** language.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/projectmgr.md:66
#, no-wrap
msgid "You have, for example, the possibility to open contextually when opening the editor a side buffer with *NvimTree* with the command `NvimTreeToggle`.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/projectmgr.md:68
#, no-wrap
msgid "> Startup Command (optional): NvimTreeToggle\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/projectmgr.md:70
#, no-wrap
msgid "Or to run a command before closing the editor.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/projectmgr.md:72
#, no-wrap
msgid "> Exit Command (optional):\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/projectmgr.md:74
#, no-wrap
msgid "Commands should be entered by omitting the colon `:` used to run the same commands in the *statusline.*\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/projectmgr.md:76
#, no-wrap
msgid "Once the configuration is finished, your project will be available in the buffer. To open it, select it and press <kbd>Enter</kbd>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/projectmgr.md:78
#, no-wrap
msgid "![ProjectMgr Add](./images/projectmgr_add.png)\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/projectmgr.md:80
#, no-wrap
msgid "As you can see from the screenshot in the **Config & Info** section, the plugin has recognized the folder as managed by *Git* and provides us with some information about it.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/projectmgr.md:82
#, no-wrap
msgid "Editing a project is done with <kbd>Ctrl</kbd> + <kbd>e</kbd> and consists of a new interactive loop, while any deletion is accomplished with the combination <kbd>Ctrl</kbd> + <kbd>d</kbd>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/projectmgr.md:83
#, no-wrap
msgid "Additional functions"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/projectmgr.md:86
#, no-wrap
msgid "The plugin provides some additional functions specified in the [dedicated section](https://github.com/charludo/projectmgr.nvim#%EF%B8%8F-configuration). The most interesting ones are the ability to synchronize a git repository when opening the project and the ability to store the status of the editor when closing it. Both features are already present in the default configuration file, although, the functionality regarding *Git* is disabled.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/projectmgr.md:88
#, no-wrap
msgid "To add repository synchronization when opening projects you will need to add the following code to the initial plugin configuration:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (lua)
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/projectmgr.md:89
#, no-wrap
msgid "config = function()\n"
"    require(\"projectmgr\").setup({\n"
"        autogit = {\n"
"            enabled = true,\n"
"            command = \"git pull --ff-only >> .git/fastforward.log 2>&1\",\n"
"        },\n"
"    })\n"
"end,\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/projectmgr.md:101
#, no-wrap
msgid "As you can see from the code the `require(\"projectmgr\").setup` function is called, which allows you to override the default settings. Anything you set inside it will change how it works.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/projectmgr.md:103
#, no-wrap
msgid "The `git pull --ff-only` command performs a *fast forward* synchronization of the repository, downloading only those files that have no conflicts and can be updated without intervention on your part.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/projectmgr.md:105
#, no-wrap
msgid "The result of the command also is directed to the file **.git/fastforward.log** to prevent it from being displayed on the terminal where NvChad is running and to have a synchronization history available.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/projectmgr.md:107
#, no-wrap
msgid "Also provided is the option to save the session when it closes. This allows you to return to the pages you were working on by selecting the project and opening it again.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (lua)
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/projectmgr.md:108
#, no-wrap
msgid "session = { enabled = true, file = \"Session.vim\" },\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/projectmgr.md:113
#, no-wrap
msgid "This option is enabled by default but it writes the **Session.vim** file to the *root* directory of the project and this is not desirable in the case of Rocky Linux documentation. In this example, it is saved in the `.git` folder which is not under version control.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/projectmgr.md:115
#, no-wrap
msgid "Adjust the path of **Session.vim** and **fastforward.log** according to your needs.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/projectmgr.md:117
#, no-wrap
msgid "Once the changes are complete, your configuration should look as follows:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (lua)
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/projectmgr.md:118
#, no-wrap
msgid "{\n"
"    \"charludo/projectmgr.nvim\",\n"
"    lazy = false, -- important!\n"
"    config = function()\n"
"        require(\"projectmgr\").setup({\n"
"            autogit = {\n"
"                enabled = true,\n"
"                command = \"git pull --ff-only > .git/fastforward.log 2>&1\",\n"
"            },\n"
"            session = { enabled = true, file = \".git/Session.vim\" },\n"
"        })\n"
"    end,\n"
"},\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/projectmgr.md:135
#, no-wrap
msgid "Now each time you open your projects, updated files will be automatically downloaded from the Git repository and you will have the latest files you were working on open in the editor ready for editing.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/projectmgr.md:139
#, no-wrap
msgid "    Open files in NvChad's saved session buffers are not automatically updated.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/projectmgr.md:141
#, no-wrap
msgid "To check if the open files do not match those updated from the repository you can use the `:checktime` command, which checks if the files open in the editor have been modified outside NvChad and alerts you to the need to update the buffers.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ###
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/projectmgr.md:142
#, no-wrap
msgid "Mapping"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/projectmgr.md:145
#, no-wrap
msgid "To speed up the opening of your projects, you can create a keyboard shortcut to put in your mapping in **/custom/mapping.lua**. An example might be:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Fenced code block (lua)
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/projectmgr.md:146
#, no-wrap
msgid "-- Projects\n"
"M.projects = {\n"
"  n = {\n"
"    [\"<leader>fp\"] = { \"<cmd> ProjectMgr<CR>\", \"Open Projects\"}\n"
"    },\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/projectmgr.md:156
#, no-wrap
msgid "With the editor in the **NORMAL** state you can open the project manager with the combination <kbd>Space</kbd> + <kbd>f</kbd> followed by <kbd>p</kbd>.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/projectmgr.md:160
#, no-wrap
msgid "As the number of projects you are working on increases, it might be useful to have a tool to help you manage them all. This plugin will allow you to speed up your work by reducing the time it takes to access the files you need to edit.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../src/docs/books/nvchad/plugins/projectmgr.md:161
#, no-wrap
msgid "We should also point out the excellent integration with `Telescope` which makes project management very functional.\n"
msgstr ""

